  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Polycystic ovary syndrome is the major cause of anovulatory infertility. Clomiphene citrate
      is the most commonly used oral agent for ovulation induction in this group, but there are
      some drawbacks with the use of it.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
